    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix SE2I_TBS function calculation and type consistency issues\n\n### Summary\nThe SE2I_TBS function in lte_mcs.c had multiple issues causing incorrect I_TBS index calculations. The function was returning wrong TBS indices due to:\n1. Invalid initialization of I_TBS to -1 (unsigned char wraps to 255)\n2. Incorrect throughput calculation formula with unnecessary 1024 scaling\n3. Improper diff calculation that didn't properly handle absolute differences\n4. Type inconsistency between implementation (unsigned char) and headers (uint8_t)\n\nUnder certain SE/N_PRB/symbPerRB combinations, this caused the function to return I_TBS indices that were significantly different from the expected target throughput.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/lte_mcs.c`: Fixed SE2I_TBS function implementation\n  - Changed return type and parameters from unsigned char to uint8_t for consistency\n  - Fixed I_TBS initialization from -1 to 0\n  - Corrected throughput calculation formula to SE * N_PRB * symbPerRB * 12\n  - Fixed absolute difference calculation for finding closest TBS match\n  - Properly initialized diffOld after throughPutGoal calculation\n\n"
}